Information We Collect

• Personal Data: We do not collect any personally identifiable information (such as your name or email address) through this app.
• Usage Data: Anonymous usage data (such as study session lengths, feature usage, and device type) may be collected to help us improve the app’s functionality and user experience.
• Device Information: The app may collect device information such as operating system version, device model, and language settings for troubleshooting and analytics.

How We Use Information

• To provide and maintain app functionality.
• To analyze usage so we can improve our app.
• To respond to user requests for support.

Data Storage & Security

• Your study session data and settings are stored locally on your device, unless you choose to use optional cloud features.
• We take reasonable measures to protect your data from unauthorized access, alteration, or disclosure.

Third-Party Services

• Our app does not share your personal information with third parties.
• If third-party services (such as analytics or crash reporting) are used, only anonymized, non-personal data is shared.

Children’s Privacy

Our app is not intended for children under the age of 13, and we do not knowingly collect any information from children under 13.

Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted here, and the date above will be updated to reflect the latest revision.

Contact Us

If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us
